{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Isa|6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","chapter":6,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:6:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":6,"verse":1,"text":"In the year that King Uzziah died, I saw the Lord seated on a high and lofty throne, and the hem of his robe filled the temple.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:6:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":6,"verse":2,"text":"Seraphim were standing above him; they each had six wings: with two they covered their faces, with two they covered their feet, and with two they flew.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:6:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":6,"verse":3,"text":"And one called to another: Holy, holy, holy is the Lord of Armies; his glory fills the whole earth.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:6:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":6,"verse":4,"text":"The foundations of the doorways shook at the sound of their voices, and the temple was filled with smoke.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:6:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":6,"verse":5,"text":"Then I said: Woe is me for I am ruined because I am a man of unclean lips and live among a people of unclean lips, and because my eyes have seen the King, the Lord of Armies.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:6:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":6,"verse":6,"text":"Then one of the seraphim flew to me, and in his hand was a glowing coal that he had taken from the altar with tongs.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:6:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":6,"verse":7,"text":"He touched my mouth with it and said: Now that this has touched your lips, your iniquity is removed and your sin is atoned for.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:6:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":6,"verse":8,"text":"Then I heard the voice of the Lord asking: Who will I send? Who will go for us? I said: Here I am. Send me.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:6:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":6,"verse":9,"text":"And he replied: Go! Say to these people: Keep listening, but do not understand; keep looking, but do not perceive.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:6:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":6,"verse":10,"text":"Make the minds of these people dull; deafen their ears and blind their eyes; otherwise they might see with their eyes and hear with their ears, understand with their minds, turn back, and be healed.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:6:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":6,"verse":11,"text":"Then I said, “Until when, Lord?” And he replied: Until cities lie in ruins without inhabitants, houses are without people, the land is ruined and desolate,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:6:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":6,"verse":12,"text":"and the Lord drives the people far away, leaving great emptiness in the land.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:6:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":6,"verse":13,"text":"Though a tenth will remain in the land, it will be burned again. Like the terebinth or the oak that leaves a stump when felled, the holy seed is the stump.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","chapter":6,"paragraphStarts":[1,4,5,6,8,9,10,11,12,13],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Isaiah’s Call and Mission"}],"poetryBlocks":[{"beforeVerse":10,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":12,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":13,"level":1}],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:6:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"In the year that King Uzziah "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 15:1","book":"2Ki","chapter":15,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 1:1","book":"Isa","chapter":1,"verse":1,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 14:28","book":"Isa","chapter":14,"verse":28,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" died, I saw the Lord "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 32:30","book":"Gen","chapter":32,"verse":30,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 3:1–6","book":"Exo","chapter":3,"verse":1,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 24:9–10","book":"Exo","chapter":24,"verse":9,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jos 5:13–15","book":"Jos","chapter":5,"verse":13,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 22:19","book":"1Ki","chapter":22,"verse":19,"letter":"h"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 31:3","book":"Isa","chapter":31,"verse":3,"letter":"i"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 1:18","book":"Jhn","chapter":1,"verse":18,"letter":"j"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 4:24","book":"Jhn","chapter":4,"verse":24,"letter":"k"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 12:41","book":"Jhn","chapter":12,"verse":41,"letter":"l"},{"kind":"text","text":" seated on a high and lofty "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 52:13","book":"Isa","chapter":52,"verse":13,"letter":"m"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 57:15","book":"Isa","chapter":57,"verse":15,"letter":"n"},{"kind":"text","text":" throne, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 9:7","book":"Psa","chapter":9,"verse":7,"letter"